DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       RIPEMD-160 is a cryptographic hash function with a 160 bit
       output.

       RIPEMD160() computes the RIPEMD-160 message digest of the
       nn bytes at dd and places it in mmdd (which must have space
       for RIPEMD160_DIGEST_LENGTH == 20 bytes of output). If mmdd
       is NULL, the digest is placed in a static array.

       The following functions may be used if the message is not
       completely stored in memory:

       RIPEMD160_Init() initializes a RRIIPPEEMMDD116600_CCTTXX structure.

       RIPEMD160_Update() can be called repeatedly with chunks of
       the message to be hashed (lleenn bytes at ddaattaa).

       RIPEMD160_Final() places the message digest in mmdd, which
       must have space for RIPEMD160_DIGEST_LENGTH == 20 bytes of
       output, and erases the RRIIPPEEMMDD116600_CCTTXX.

       Applications should use the higher level functions
       EVP_DigestInit(3) etc. instead of calling the hash
       functions directly.

